main event: A naval tug boat sighted an unidentified flying object (UFO) moving at a high rate of speed towards the coast.
interesting points: The UFO was flying northwest to southeast at a variable speed, at an altitude of approximately 6,000 feet.
The UFO was flying at a very high rate of speed and at the same time extremely low or within 100 feet of the water.
The sighting was reported to multiple military entities, including the Navy, Air Force, and Coast Guard.
The report notes that this may be a duplicate of a previous report (AF IN 33444 on May 26, 1963).
The report is incomplete, with the duration of the sighting and the manner of disappearance not reported.
